ndamental insights into one of the most innovative and influential cultural moments of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aMotion pictureszItalyxHistory. 0aRealism in motion pictures. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aElio Vittorini.  aFascism.  aItalian Film.  aItalian Literature.  aItalo Calvino.  aItaly.  aLuchino Visconti.  aNeorealism.  aRoberto Rossellini.  aVittorio De Sica.  aartistic movements.  acultural history.  amodern art.  arealism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106904530 cprintz978148750710740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753557540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487535575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487535575/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070474-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020